      "comment": "UNCLE CRAIGO (1) has the hoof on the till after placing in his last four outings, last week leading and fighting well to go under narrowly. Has the speed to take advantage of the ace draw so could prove hard to catch. PIRANI PRINCESS (3) in in good form, coming from the back row to score two back at Albury before a third from this barrier here last start, beaten less than 5 metres in a higher-graded race. Could give this a mighty shake. VALENTINI (2) draws well and could find the form that saw her score back-to-back wins last month. SOKYS FALCON (8) draws wide again but must be respected after putting two wins together, the latest at this circuit and distance.",
